{"TopicId":110672,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.0.x, DISCONTINUED] Control Surface Action Groups - Tweak Control surfaces in flight via action groups! [May 24]","CreatedByName":"iPeer","CreatedById":106092,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-24T18:58:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"iPeer","CreatedById":106092,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-24T18:58:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOriginally suggested by \u003Ca href=\u0022http://twitch.tv/Kofeyh\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKofeyh\u003C/a\u003E of \u003Ca href=\u0022http://twitch.tv/KSPTV\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKSPTV\u003C/a\u003E, this mod allows players to assign enabling or disabling of Roll, Pitch and/or Yaw to action groups so they can be switched easily during flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, these are available as part of \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/100932\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EActions Everywhere\u003C/a\u003E by Diazo, however, AE is a lot more in depth. This mod only focuses on Control Surfaces. If you want a wider range of groups, or compatibility with FAR, consider using that instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENot currently compatible with FAR. If you want these action groups to work with FAR, consider using \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/100932\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EActions Everywhere\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E instead.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Ieqi4Go.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Ieqi4Go.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRequires \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/55219\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EModule Manager\u